u0627\u0644\u064e\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":6183,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/09\/10\/greet-peace-do-not-know\/","url_meta":{"origin":15256,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Islam: Greet strangers with peace","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"September 10, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Abdullah ibn Amr\u00a0reported: A man asked the Prophet, \u201cWhich Islam is best?\u201d The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cThat you feed the hungry and you greet with peace those you know and those you do not know.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 28, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 39 Grade:\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Featured&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Featured","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/featured\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":784,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2011\/05\/15\/ahl-al-bayt-eat-fill\/","url_meta":{"origin":15256,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Food: The Prophet\u2019s family rarely ate to their fill","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 15, 2011","format":false,"excerpt":"Aisha reported: The family of Muhammad, peace and blessings be upon him,\u00a0never ate to their fill of wheat bread for three consecutive nights, ever since they had come to Medina, until he passed away. Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 6089, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 2970 Grade: Muttafaqun Alayhi\u00a0(authenticity agreed upon) according to Al-Bukhari and\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&qu